pod_farm.guide.animals.1: Bison live in plains, and love to eat wheat. Be careful, though; when the Bison gets hurt, it will get scared and attack you!%1
pod_farm.guide.animals.11: The Peacock, with its imposing feathers, can mainly be found in plains and forests, where it likes to eat Beans, Broccoli, Lettuce, and also Kohlrabi.%1
pod_farm.guide.animals.13: If you find a weird sparkled egg on the ground, it is likely that there is also a Quail around. You will find them pecking for seeds in savannas, deserts, plains, and forests.%1
pod_farm.guide.animals.15: The Turkey lives in relatively cold regions; you can find it in ice plains, the taiga, and the snowy taiga. They are searching for berries and seeds to eat all day long!%1
pod_farm.guide.animals.17: Yaks love the mountains and are commonly found in snowy slopes, frozen peaks, meadows, and extreme hills. They eat wheat and are another source of milk! But be careful; they will get scared and attack you if they get hurt!%1%1
pod_farm.guide.animals.3: Crows will try to break your crops. You can build Scarecrows to scare them away!%1
pod_farm.guide.animals.5: Deers often hide in Forests, but sometimes, when looking for berries, they also come out onto plains or meadows.%1
pod_farm.guide.animals.7: Ducks prefer living near the water. You will find them around rivers and swamps; sometimes, they fly! They only come to land to look for seeds to eat.%1
pod_farm.guide.animals.9: Geese have similar preferences as ducks. They also live in rivers and swamps! But unlike the duck, geese eat berries in addition to seeds.%1
pod_farm.guide.animals.title: Animals
pod_farm.guide.changelog.1.0.10: -Fixed Bean textures showing incorrectly%1-Fixed Peach Pie showing up as Apple Pie on the Plate%1-Fixed Apple Pie not showing up on the Plate%1-Fixed bone meal creating grass when used on plants in creative mode%1-Fixed Coconuts immediately breaking when spawning randomly in the world%1-Fixed Players not being able to open doors while holding seeds%1-Fixed the Cheeseburger recipe containing too much iron (and consuming a Bucket)%1-Fixed the dupe issue with Watering Cans when placed on specific blocks%1-Fire Aspect weapons now cook meat when used to kill an animal
pod_farm.guide.changelog.1.0.11: -Adjusted Mob Loot drops to match vanilla animals%1-Fixed Coconuts dropping items when naturally despawning%1-Yak & Bison can now be leashed%1-Fixed multiple plates being able to be stacked on one block%1-Fixed projectiles being able to break crops%1-Fix crops sometimes starting to float%1-Adjust Spawn Rates of different mobs%1-Added missing crafting recipes for all crops to be turned into seeds%1-Yak & Bison no longer break snow%1-Added a setting to disable mob trampling of crops and blocks
pod_farm.guide.changelog.1.0.12: -Added Cooking Pot%1-Added Cooking Pan%1-Added Fridge%1-Added Grill%1-Added Kettle%1-Added Oven%1-Added Stove%1-Added Toaster%1-Added Blender%1-Added Smoothies%1-Added Milkshakes%1-Added Toast%1-Added Cookbook%1-All drinks can now be placed on the ground%1-All tin cans can now be placed on the ground%1-All jars can now be placed on the ground%1-Added 'Kitchenware' Page to the Guide Book%1-Removed 'Furnace Recipes' Page from the Guide Book (Recipes can now be found in the Cookbook)%1-Removed 'Brewing Recipes' Page from the Guide Book (Recipes can now be found in the Cookbook)%1-Removed Food Items from 'Crafting Recipes' Page from the Guide Book (Recipes can now be found in the Cookbook)%1-Moved Popcorn to the Miscellaneous Food section the the creative inventory%1-Moved Cooked Corn to the Miscellaneous Food section the the creative inventory%1-Improved Crow Spawning Setting%1-Added a check that will despawn quail eggs if they are stuck
pod_farm.guide.changelog.1.0.8: -Peach Trees spawn rate increased%1-Grape Vines spawn rate increased%1-Corn now gets checked after placement%1-Changed every crops hit-box to be 1 block wide%1-Added crafting recipe to allow fruits to be turned into saplings%1-Reduced validation limit to 20 crops per player per validation. (performance optimisation)%1-Increased validations more frequent from 30 ticks -> 6 ticks. (performance optimisation)
pod_farm.guide.changelog.1.0.9: -Added Burgers%1-Added Plates%1-Added Watering Can%1-Added a crafting recipe for wool using cotton%1-Added a furnace recipe for cooked egg using quail eggs%1-Added a crafting recipe for black dye using black feathers%1-Added "Changelog" tab to the guide book%1-Added "Settings" tab to the guide book%1-Added another variant to the Yak%1-Converted Juicer to be a Block%1-Made crops compostable%1-Made quail eggs throwable%1-Made certain crops harvestable without having to break them%1-Realigned leash locator on certain animals%1-Overhauled plenty of textures%1-Fixed certain animals not being breedable using our seeds%1-Fixed certain animals being the wrong scale when growing up
pod_farm.guide.changelog.1.1.0: - All crops, bushes, and plants have been converted to blocks.%1- Trees now have wood, stripped logs, stripped wood, and leaves for every type of tree.%1- Crops are now affected by the gamerule 'randomtickspeed'.%1- Crops will now be destroyed when moved by a piston.%1- When using bone meal in creative mode, Crops will instantly grow to their final stage. In survival mode, bone meal will still act normally.%1- Fortune enchantment now works on crops.%1- We have added the setting 'Water Breaks Crops'. If you experience performance issues, we recommend disabling this setting.%1- Added Banana Cluster.%1- Trees are now complete block structures that can grow fruits on their leaves.%1- Bananas can now be used to place banana clusters on banana logs.%1- Trees will generate as complete structures worldwide, but only in unexplored chunks. (In existing worlds, all chunks, including those previously explored, count as unexplored chunks).%1- Updated Crow behavior.%1- Crows now no longer break trees added by our Add-On.%1- Crows now break base Minecraft crops, such as wheat.%1- Crops, bushes and plants will automatically convert to their block versions as you get close to them.%1- Trees WILL NOT convert automatically. Break them to receive their sapling and replant it.%1- WARNING: Entity-based crops and trees will be removed in a future update, so we recommend replacing them as soon as possible.
pod_farm.guide.changelog.1.1.1: - Fixed certain crops dropping seeds when being "picked"%1- Reduced amount of bananas dropped by banana cluster from 2-3 to 1-2%1- Reduced amount of sweet potatoes dropped from 3 to 2-3%1- Fixed certain crops not being "pickable" when the top block was clicked%1- The Grill can now be crafted using our custom logs%1- Fish can now be put on the plate%1- Fixed the 'Animal Spawning' setting not working%1- Reduced growth speed of saplings%1- Reduced growth speed of crops%1- Reduced growth speed of leaves%1- Reduced amount of fruit dropped by leaves from 2-3 to 1-2%1- Increased speed at which leaves decay%1- All custom log and wood types can now be turned into charcoal using a furnace%1- Added a button in the cookbook that allows the player to unpin recipes
pod_farm.guide.changelog.1.2.0: - Added Spirits%1- Added Spirit Hives%1- Added Palm Tree%1- Added Mustard Plant%1- Added Mustard Bottle%1- Added Sausage%1- Added Hotdog%1- Added various Honey Mustard Meat Types%1- Added Milk Chocolate%1- Added Dark Chocolate%1- Added Chocolate Spread%1- Added Chocolate Toast%1- Added Chocolate Cake%1- Trees, Bushes & Plants will now generate using Minecraft's Chunk Generation%1- Removed 'Crop Spawning' setting%1- Adjusted breaking time of wood to match vanilla
pod_farm.guide.changelog.1.2.1: - Water will now by default break crops.%1- Removed "Water Breaks Crops" Setting.%1- Crops will now be properly colored on maps.%1- Composting uses the new component from Minecraft now. This means items can also be composted using hoppers.%1- Crops will now return their seeds when middle clicked.%1- The following Item Groups were created for Inventory Menus and items were grouped accordingly: Tin Cans, Drinks, Ice Creams, Sandwiches, Spreads, Sushi, Toasts, Baked Desserts, Bowls, Kitchenware%1- Made fruit on player placed leaves grow more reliably.%1- Added correct tags to our logs in parity with vanilla logs.%1- Made quail eggs despawn more reliably after a baby quail spawned.

pod_farm.guide.kitchenware.1: Make Smoothies, Milkshakes and Ice Cream using the Blender! Mix any food you want in your blender, click it with a glass bottle or an ice cream cone and take your food item out! Includes Milk or Oat Milk to make Milkshakes, includes a snowball and sugar to make ice cream!%1
pod_farm.guide.kitchenware.11: The juicer can be used to turn fruits into nice and refreshing juices. Once crafted, place the juicer on the ground and click it with your fruits to turn them into juice! After you have put enough fruit in the juicer, you can click it with a glass bottle and enjoy your fresh juice!%1
pod_farm.guide.kitchenware.13: Need a coffee or a tea? Craft a kettle, place it on a stove, add water and the ingredient you want to cook with, then wait for it to finish brewing your drink and click it with a glass bottle to take it out. You can brew up to 3 drinks at the same time, each water bottle you add contributes one unit of water to the kettle, each drink you take out reduces it by one unit. You can also place the kettle anywhere else in the world.%1
pod_farm.guide.kitchenware.15: The Oven is another alternative to the furnace which allows you to easily cook up to two food items at the same time! Click it with your raw food to put it in the oven and wait for it to be cooked, then you can punch the oven to take it back out!%1
pod_farm.guide.kitchenware.17: Plates are a cool new way to decorate your base by putting down any food item! Simply right click the plate with the item to put it in. Punch the plate to take it back out. A plate can be crafted using Quartz!%1
pod_farm.guide.kitchenware.19: The Stove is used to supply power to cooking pots, pans and kettles! Place it anywhere you want, then place the kitchenware you need on top of it and start cooking!%1
pod_farm.guide.kitchenware.21: Turn your bread slices into toast by putting them in the toaster! The toaster can toast up to two bread slices at the same time. Click it to add a bread slice in, then once the bread slice is toasted, punch it to take it back out!%1
pod_farm.guide.kitchenware.23: Spice Mills are used to make your food tastier, but too much spice will make it less tasty. There are seven different spices you can use: chili, garlic, ginger, mustard, onion, pepper, and salt.%1
pod_farm.guide.kitchenware.3: With the Cooking Pan, you can cook your favorite food items without having to use a furnace! Simply place the cooking pan on a stove, put your raw food in it and wait for it to be cooked. Once your food is cooked, punch the pan to take it out. Optionally you can also place your cooking pan anywhere else, but cooking will only work on a stove.%1
pod_farm.guide.kitchenware.5: The Cooking Pot allows you to cook certain dishes. Put all ingredients required to cook your dish in a cooking pot, then wait for it to finish cooking and take it out by clicking the pot with the container in which the dish is stored in. Find out what dishes you can cook in the cooking pot in the cookbook! You can place your cooking pot anywhere in the world, but it will only cook the dish when placed on a stove.%1
pod_farm.guide.kitchenware.7: The fridge will keep all your food items fresh & cold! You can place two fridges on top of each other. While their inventories will stay separated, they will connect to a large fridge.%1
pod_farm.guide.kitchenware.9: Tired of cooked meat? Try grilling it on the Grill! Place your grill, load it up with coal or charcoal, ignite it with a flint and steel and put your raw meat on it by clicking it. Punch the grill to take your grilled meat off once it's done! You can put up to two pieces of meat on the grill at the same time.%1
pod_farm.guide.kitchenware.title: Kitchenware
pod_farm.guide.main.book: If you lose the book, you can re-craft it with a book and a §awheat§r. You can also access this guide with the command §7/podfarm§r at anytime.
pod_farm.guide.main.intro: §rThe Farming Add-On, add 37 new crops, 160+ new consumables, 9 new animals, and much more! This book will teach you everything you need to know!
pod_farm.guide.main.support: For more detailed information and support, check out §o§shttps://pdcr.sh/farm§r
pod_farm.guide.main.title: FARMING Add-On
pod_farm.guide.misc.body: On this page you will find information about various helpful features and utilities in the Farming Add-On.
pod_farm.guide.misc.decorations.body: Many items can be placed to be used as decoration. Place any drink, ice cream, bowl, tin can, spice mill or jar on the ground to decorate your world! All other food items can be placed on plates and will have a 3D Model too!
pod_farm.guide.misc.decorations.title: Decorations
pod_farm.guide.misc.scarecrows.body:
Crows want to eat your crops, but instead of scaring them yourself all day long, you can build a scarecrow to protect your crops. A Scarecrow will scare all crows within an 8 block radius.

§lConstruction§r

Place a fence on the bottom, then a hay block above, after adding two fences as arms to the side of the hay block, place a carved pumpkin on top, and your scarecrow will be done!
pod_farm.guide.misc.scarecrows.title: Scarecrows
pod_farm.guide.misc.title: Miscellaneous
pod_farm.guide.misc.watering_can.body: The Watering Can allows you to make your crops grow faster! Interact with crops to water them, once your watering can is empty, simply click a water block to refill! Sneak while using your watering can to place it down.
pod_farm.guide.misc.watering_can.title: Watering Can
pod_farm.guide.other.11: Spirits are little helpers in your world that will make farming easier for you. They spawn from spirit hives whenever there's something for them to do within a radius of 15 blocks. They will harvest or pick crops, bushes and fruits on trees and bring the loot back to their hive.%1
pod_farm.guide.other.13: Spirit Hives can be crafted using hay bales, blocks of amethyst and a hopper. Place a Spirit Hive around your farm to have spirits spawn and harvest for you. When you place a block container above the Spirit Hive with seeds in it, spirits will take those seeds to plant new crops on empty farmland. Harvested items will be brought back to the hive and will be either dropped on the floor, or, if there is a block container below the Spirit Hive, they will be deposited into that container. The sides of a spirit hive should be left open as spirits will spawn here. A Spirit Hive can spawn up to 5 spirits. For Trees to be harvested, the trees need to be within a 15 block radius of the spirit hive. For all other plants to be harvested, they have to be within a 15 block horizontal radius, and a 2 block vertical radius.%1%1
pod_farm.guide.other.5: All Drinks added by this Add-On can be placed on the ground!%1
pod_farm.guide.other.7: All Tin Cans added by this Add-On can be placed on the ground! Stack up to four tin cans of the same kind on one block!%1
pod_farm.guide.other.9: All Jars added by this Add-On can be placed on the ground! Stack up to two jars of the same kind on one block!%1
